content.shortDescription: When the mysterious deep space research vessel USCSS Maginot crash-lands on Earth, Wendy and a ragtag group of tactical soldiers make a fateful discovery that puts them face-to-face with the planet's greatest threat.
content.title: Alien: Earth

textRecommendations.headline: A show that is both an escape and a confrontation with the future
textRecommendations.body: In some ways, the show is an escape. It’s action, horror, and science fiction entertainment. It’s bigger than life and also a fairy tale about how children grow up. But there’s also an urgency to it because it feels like you’re looking at your own future and the future of this planet, and it's troublesome. So I think you can both escape into it or leave it with things to think about.

profile.bio: Despite working on multiple movies, Noah Hawley really grabbed the world’s attention with his role as creator of the TV show “Fargo” (2014–2024). He was an accomplished television writer before that series, having worked on shows such as “Bones” (2005–2008), “The Unusuals” (2009), and “My Generation” (2010). Fargo marked his first step into directing, which he quickly followed up by serving as creator for the surreal superhero show “Legion” (2017–2019) and developing “Alien: Earth” (2025) for FX in which he is showrunner, writer, and director. His feature film directorial debut is the psychological drama “Lucy in the Sky” (2019), which saw him work with Natalie Portman, Jon Hamm, and Colman Domingo. Hawley is a successful writer and director in the entertainment industry, but he is also a writer with six novels to his name and an accomplished singer.

textRecommendations.headline: An epic, intimate, and engaging story set in the world of Alien
textRecommendations.body: This show is really smart and really entertaining. Usually when you get something this vast, you don’t get something this grounded. The combination of those two things makes it a great show, and I'm very proud to be a part of it.

profile.bio: If you’ve seen the smash hit series “Justified” (2010–2015), then you won’t need any introduction to the man who embodied lead character Raylan Givens. Timothy Olyphant is known for his other major television roles in “Deadwood” (2004–2006), “Santa Clarita Diet” (2017–2019), “Fargo” (2020), “Stick” (2025), and “Alien: Earth” (2025). He has also starred in multiple feature films, such as “Snowden” (2016), “Once Upon a Time in Hollywood” (2019), “Amsterdam” (2022), and “Havoc” (2025). He has performed in major stage productions, voiced characters in video games, and won multiple awards throughout an illustrious and prolific career in the entertainment industry.

textRecommendations.headline: An Alien experience for newcomers and diehard fans alike
textRecommendations.body: People who have never explored the world of Alien will really enjoy this piece because it will be fresh and new. For the people who already enjoy the Alien franchise, I hope they will feel the love, honor, and respect that Noah and this entire production have for the original film and the franchise as a whole, while also being able to experience something pretty unique. It’s a really cool show!

profile.bio: After a compelling debut performance in Olivia Wilde’s thriller “Don’t Worry Darling” (2022), Sydney Chandler announced herself as an actress to keep an eye on. She has since starred in the miniseries “Pistol” (2022), the Apple TV+ series “Sugar” (2025) alongside Colin Farrell, and “Alien: Earth” (2025), where she has a leading role as the character Wendy.

textRecommendations.headline: A show that transcends genre to bring a human story to the Alien universe
textRecommendations.body: This show is a genre piece in every dimension. It is horror in many different iterations while also being a thriller. Ultimately, it is an innately human story and one that is truly irresistible.

profile.bio: Esteemed executive producer David W. Zucker is known for bringing the beloved show, “The Good Wife” (2009–2015), to the small screen. His executive producer credits range from shows like “Kaleidoscope” (2023), “Raised by Wolves” (2020–2022), and “Great Expectations” (2023) to series like “The Good Fight” (2021–2022) and “Alien: Earth” (2025). He is the CCO of Scott Free Productions and has worked with multiple platforms such as BBC, FX, HBO, AMC, National Geographic, and more.
